Frontend
1. create client folder
2. npx create-react-app . => if we do not write dot then it will create another folder inside 
   client and will place all setup files in that folder
3. npm i
4. npm start
5. clean or simplify app.js, app.css, index.css, index.js
6. setup tailwind => install tailwind via npm 
     -> npm install -D tailwindcss@npm:@tailwindcss/postcss7-compat postcss@^7 autoprefixer@^9
7. install and configure CRACO => npm install @craco/craco
8. make changes in script from tailwind installation
9. make file craco.config.js
10. generate your tailwind.config.js file: => npx tailwindcss-cli@latest init
11. add content in index.css
12. install react router dom to navigate => npm i react-router-dom
13. install react icons => npm i react-icons
14. npm i classnames
15. npm i react-slick
16. npm install slick-carousel => for carousel
17. npm i react-rating-stars-component => star ratings
18. npm i leaflet react-leaflet   => install react leaflet for map
19. delete cache folder from node modules , in package.json - makes changes in browserlist
20. react image viewer => npm i react-images-viewer
21. Redux => yarn add redux react-redux
22. Redux thunk to make asynchronous task and logger for console log => 
      yarn add redux-thunk redux-logger
23. yarn add axios
24. yarn add dayjs
25. yarn add gravatar



Concepts or links ->
1. color =>  https://smart-swatch.netlify.app/
2. react icons => https://react-icons.github.io/react-icons/
3. classnames => https://www.npmjs.com/package/classnames
4. react slick npm => https://www.npmjs.com/package/react-slick
5. react rating => https://www.npmjs.com/package/react-rating-stars-component
6. react rating star component => 
      https://www.npmjs.com/package/react-rating-stars-component
7. leaflet map react => https://react-leaflet.js.org/
8. npm i @headlessui/react
9. react image viewer => https://www.npmjs.com/package/react-images-viewer
10. axios default configuration => https://axios-http.com/docs/config_defaults
11. gravatar api => https://www.npmjs.com/package/gravatar-api
12. razorpay docs => https://razorpay.com/docs/
13. razorpay npm => https://www.npmjs.com/package/razorpay
install rozorpay in server

*Redux - connect our frontend to backend , to manage all the data
*state managment - state means data
*prop-drilling - 
*global store - components can easily access data from global store but not direct it will done by reducer
*react(component) -----> Action means js function -----> reducer(managers) -----> golbal store
reducer request to global store. global store will pass info to ---> reducer --> pass to --> action ---> pass to  ----> component
*Redux uses state management. We are using redux avoid prop drilling
*Use switch statement to manage all the individual pieces of global store
*Redux by default doesn't support asynchronous task
* we need logger only in development mode not in production mode
*Thunk use to return object from async function
